<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2014/06/02/spring-boot-1-1-0-rc1-available-now">Spring Boot 1.1.0.RC1 Available Now</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon releases"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/releases">Releases</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/ae671230e3a1c2a0eefa7604990084f1?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<a class="author" href="/team/dsyer">Dave Syer</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2014-06-02 08:10:38.629">June 2, 2014</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="1618" href="/blog/2014/06/02/spring-boot-1-1-0-rc1-available-now#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Spring Boot 1.1.0.RC1 is available now in the Spring repositories. There are some new features and some new <a href="https://docs.spring.io/spring-boot/docs/current-SNAPSHOT/reference/htmlsingle">documentation</a>:</p>
<ul>
<li><p>Autoconfiguration support for Spring Data Elastic Search, HornetQ messaging, Spring Social</p></li>
<li><p>Support for <code>@IntegrationTest</code> in the Groovy CLI</p></li>
<li><p>Upgrades to Tomcat, Spring Integration, Reactor and Groovy</p></li>
</ul>
<p>We are on schedule for a GA release some time in the next 2 weeks, so please try out the RC1 and get feedback onto github as soon as you have time.</p>
</div>
</section>
